{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Gym"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"InvertedPendulum","externalID":"s:3Gym16InvertedPendulumC","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InvertedPendulum"}],"symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"InvertedPendulum"}]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/init()"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/data","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/model"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/Env-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Description","type":"heading","anchor":"Description","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart."}]},{"text":"Action Space","type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The action space is a continuous ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(action)"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[-3, 3]"},{"text":", where ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"action"},{"text":" represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"force and sign representing the direction)","type":"text"}]},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Action","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Min","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Max","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Force applied on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Force (N)","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"text":"Observation Space","type":"heading","anchor":"Observation-Space","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The observation is a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with shape ","type":"text"},{"code":"(4,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" where the elements correspond to the following:","type":"text"}]},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Observation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Max","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"position of the cart along the linear surface","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position (m)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"angle (rad)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"linear velocity of the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"velocity (m\/s)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"text":"Rewards","type":"heading","anchor":"Rewards","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pole is upright."}]},{"text":"Starting State","type":"heading","anchor":"Starting-State","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All observations start in state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity."}]},{"text":"Episode End","type":"heading","anchor":"Episode-End","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Arguments","type":"heading","anchor":"Arguments","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No additional arguments are currently supported.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Version History","type":"heading","anchor":"Version-History","level":3},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym":{"title":"Gym","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gym","type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"collection"},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/InvertedPendulum":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"InvertedPendulum","url":"\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum","role":"symbol","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/InvertedPendulum/init()":{"url":"\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum\/init()","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4